Solvang’s future scientists score at County Science Fair

SYVNEWS.COM
Solvang’s future scientists score at County Science Fair

post_text: For the first time in recent memory, Solvang School took a team to the Santa Barbara County Science Fair and did very well. Fernanda Barbosa, Andrew Bunke, Audrey Fuette, Tessa Haws and Harry Mullin all represented our school well after being recognized for having outstanding projects at the Solvang School Science Fair. At the county fair, Fernanda won for outstanding project in Electronics or Computers, Tessa received a bronze medal in Botany and Zoology, and Audrey won a gold medal in the Molecular Biology, Chemistry and Microbiology Division, received the Independent Scientist Award, and was selected to represent the county at the California State Science Fair! Congratulations to these fantastic students and to their teacher, our very own Dr. Erin Dunkle.
text: For the first time in recent memory, Solvang School took a team to the Santa Barbara County Science Fair and did very well. Fernanda Barbosa, Andrew Bunke, Audrey Fuette, Tessa Haws and Harry Mullin all represented our school well after being recognized for having outstanding projects at the Solvang School Science Fair. At the county fair, Fernanda won for outstanding project in Electronics or Computers, Tessa received a bronze medal in Botany and Zoology, and Audrey won a gold medal in the Molecular Biology, Chemistry and Microbiology Division, received the Independent Scientist Award, and was selected to represent the county at the California State Science Fair! Congratulations to these fantastic students and to their teacher, our very own Dr. Erin Dunkle.

post_text:
Please join us tonight, October 10, 7:00-8:00 p.m. to hear about Gifted education at Solvang Elementary School. Dr. Dina Brulles will be our guest speaker. The presentation will take place in the cafeteria. All parents are welcome.

Dina Brulles, Ph.D., is the Director of Gifted Education at Paradise Valley Unified School District where she has developed a continuum of gifted education programs, preschool through high school. The programs and services Dina oversees incorporate innovative uses of technology, enfranchise underrepresented populations and provide extensive professional development opportunities. She is also the Gifted Program Coordinator at Arizona State University.
